The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Briefs

 The 

 estate manager of the urban development department, Deepak 

 Gupta, on Thursday chased and caught a man who had attempted 

 to burgle his apartment at Labony, in Salt Lake. hile entering 

 the building in the afternoon, Gupta noticed a man in a courier 

 company?s uniform leaving the premises. When he found the 

 lock on his main door broken, he pursued the man and caught 

 him near Labony island. 

 A 

 newborn abandoned by his mother died at Medical College and 

 Hospital on Thursday morning. Uma Devi, 24, a pavement dweller, 

 left the hospital after giving birth on Monday. On Thursday 

 afternoon, she returned to inquire about the baby and was 

 told of his death. 

 Shankar 

 Das, in his mid 40s, was killed when a Matador knocked him 

 down at the Shyambazar five-point crossing on Wednesday night. 

 Das was taken to RG Kar Medical College and Hospital. The 

 driver fled with his vehicle. 

 Anita 

 Roy, 21, an inmate of Liluah Home was found hanging from the 

 ceiling of her room on Thursday afternoon. The body has been 

 sent for post-mortem. 

 Eastern Railway will run two pairs of special trains between 

 Howrah and New Delhi. The trains will leave Howrah on June 

 30 and July 2. 




